caption: Amazing place to have party and go drunk without regrets after a hard exam. Highly recommended!

This lake is little-known, like all the other lakes in the Bois de Boulogne, it is very pleasant to walk all along, there are waterfalls, a chalet on the island and a river shuttle to get there. Not far from there is the upper lake, the contour is not currently possible, there is work, it could be pointed out that it is not possible to go around it, that would avoid to get lost. A plan is very useful for evolving in the Bois de Boulogne, the risk is to miss some very pretty things, it is so vast.

Lac Inferieur is the largest body of water in the Bois de Boulogne. Built in 1854 under Napoleon III, it allows you to enjoy splendid landscapes immersed in the nature of the Parisian park. A rowing boat trip on the lake allows you to enjoy every glimpse of this place, it is definitely worth the effort of rowing!

Very beautiful lake in the Bois de Boulogne. Always a pleasure to stroll there, go boating, walk around the lake, enjoy the view. Really lucky to be able to have this time of break and silence next to a city as active as Paris.

A romantic place you could wish for. The lake offers lovely walks, as well as the possibility of boating. You can also picnic on the banks in fine weather. A Parisian parenthesis, a bubble a stone’s throw from the center of the capital
I don't know a more beautiful and serene place than the Lower Lake, with its birds, its turtles and its two islands.
Magnificent place for walks, extremely busy on weekends but remains very quiet during off-peak hours and during the week
By bike or on foot around the Lower Lake of Bois de Boulogne is a treat.... When the weather is good, public holidays and weekends are very lively...

Perfect for recovery jogging and walking around. A real corner of nature near the ring road. Too bad the water and the bottom are not clean. Lack of aquatic life.

The walk is very pleasant around the lake, especially when it's a little hot. Possibility of renting a boat (please bring a deposit check of €50). The only regret is that the number of parks in or around Paris is very limited for 2 million inhabitants (excluding nearby suburbs), and the paths are very crowded, which spoils the nature experience a little.

The large lake of Bois de Boulogne, called "lower lake" is an idyllic place for walks. A pedestrian path follows its banks as closely as possible, while cyclists and mounted police have overhanging trails.

A real lung in Paris. Ideal with family or friends, alone or as a couple. Pleasant in all seasons.

So close to Paris a very romantic haven of peace. The trees are magnificent, the fauna very alive with very welcoming coypu. To have.
